The author, Emily Hardman, is an intern in the Office of Political Affairs at the White House. She had the opportunity to assist with the Made in America Product Showcase, which aimed to highlight companies with American-made products. Emily's role included researching companies from Western states and escorting company representatives to their tables during the event. She was impressed by the diversity of products showcased, ranging from yachts to tumblers to pianos. Emily particularly enjoyed meeting the founder of the Great Alaskan Bowl Company and learning about their family business. Overall, participants and Emily herself considered the event a success in celebrating American companies.